141. The passage ‘ideo vocatur Wiclyffe nequam rita, memoriae ter dampnatae‚’ fairly puzzled me, and all the antiquaries to whom I showed it. At last I put the words before Mr. Thompson, of the MSS. department, British Museum, who suggested, after a few minutes‚ that the reading should be ‘nequam vita‚’ and that the words were a pun on Wikliff's name. The emendation is one os those happy conjectures, which instantly approve themselves, and are seen to be perfectly conclusive. It may be observed that Knyghton similarly jests on Wikliff’s name, saying that it would be more properly ‘Wicked belief!
